Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast in oven until lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Trim @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}, then halve lengthwise. Thinly slice into shreds. Peel, core, and dice @Granny Smith apple{1}(peeled, cored, and diced). Zest and halve @lemon{1}(halved and zested). In a shallow #dish{}, combine @blackening spice{1%tablespoon} and @Sugar{1%tablespoon}.

Season @boneless pork chops{12%ounce} all over with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in dish with rub and toss to coat pork evenly all over (you may have some rub left over).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest ~{5%minutes}.

While pork rests, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{3%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add Brussels sprouts and apple. Cook until Brussels sprouts browned and apples are tender, ~{5-6%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Stir in @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, a pinch of lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice (to taste). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice pork against the grain. Divide pork, sweet potato wedges, and Brussels sprout mixture between plates and serve.